%% Diagram: PostgreSQL MVCC tuple visibility across concurrent transactions
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant H as Heap (row 'A')
    participant T1 as T1 (writer)
    participant T2 as T2 (Read Committed)
    participant T3 as T3 (Repeatable Read)

    note over H: v1 {xmin=100, xmax=0}\nbalance=100 (committed)

    T1->>H: BEGIN (xid=200)
    T2->>H: BEGIN, snapshot xmin>=200 in-progress
    T3->>H: BEGIN, snapshot xmin>=200 in-progress

    T2->>H: SELECT balance
    H-->>T2: sees v1 = 100 (xmin=100 committed,\nxmax=0)

    T1->>H: UPDATE balance = 150
    note over H: v1 {xmin=100, xmax=200}\nv2 {xmin=200, xmax=0}\n(xid=200 still in-progress)

    T3->>H: SELECT balance
    H-->>T3: sees v1 = 100 (xmin=200\nnot in T3 snapshot)

    T1->>H: COMMIT

    T2->>H: SELECT balance again
    H-->>T2: sees v2 = 150 (fresh snapshot\nper statement at RC)

    T3->>H: SELECT balance again
    H-->>T3: still sees v1 = 100\n(snapshot frozen at BEGIN — no\nphantoms, no non-repeatable reads)
